    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Never published before this edition.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" n="a">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>σ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab></div>
                <div type="textpart" n="b">
                    <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ιτευ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name><supplied reason="lost">Π</supplied>ελάγων</name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Σελυμαῖος" type="patronymic"> Σ<supplied reason="lost">ελυ</supplied><unclear>μ</unclear>αίω</name></persName></persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2a"/><space quantity="4" unit="cm"/>
                </ab></div>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                    <p>a) Intraduisible.</p>
                    <p>b) <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Pelagôn fils de Sélymaios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                    <p>a) Intraduisible.</p>
                    <p>b) <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Pelagon son of Selymaios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                    <p>a) Intraducibile.</p>
                    <p>b) <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Pelagon figlio di Selymaios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p/>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>The only letter surviving from text a) is taken as a vestige of the previous text, while text b), because of its not very regular cutting and display, seems to be an appended graffito. However, this 
             distribution is not quite sure.</p>
             <p>At line 1 of text b) a possible restoration would be <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἱαριτεύοντος</foreign> in the formula of datation  'So and so being priest'. Other restorations might also be proposed.
             The names at line 2 are both rare, but attested once each in the third century BC in Cyrene: Pelagon at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr116400</ref>, Selymaios at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr008200</ref>.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
